        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 3 at 9:56PM EST by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 956 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Bainbridge to near Greater Binghamton
Airport. Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Binghamton, Johnson City, Endicott, Kirkwood, Conklin, Maine,
Sanford, Susquehanna, Nanticoke, and Deposit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
